<HEADLINE> Ethiopia, S. Africa Discuss Business Coop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 8 (Xinhua) -- South Africa has expressed
willingness to make investment in Ethiopia after a business
delegation from Johannesburg visited the Horn of Africa country.
</P>
<P>
Moelets Mbeki, who led the five-member South African
delegation, said here Thursday that his delegation had sorted out
investment areas that could be profitable both to Ethiopia and his
country.
</P>
<P>
South African entrepreneurs were keen to involve in the
construction of railway lines in Ethiopia, and to engage in the
manufacturing of footwear in Ethiopia, Mbeki said.
</P>
<P>
The delegation would "initiate a project to make leather shoe
uppers in Ethiopia and export them to South Africa", he said.
</P>
<P>
During its four-day visit beginning Sunday, the South African
business mission also had extensive discussions with Ethiopian
officials over investment in the areas of telecommunications,
natural gas development, broadcasting and advertizing, Mbeki
added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
