<HEADLINE> Army worm Invasion Curbed in Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The army worm invasion that hit
various parts of Ethiopia has been curbed, a senior official of
the Agriculture Ministry said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Some 118,753 litres and 38,561 kgs of pesticides had so far
been sprayed in the past few weeks, Crop Development and
Protection team leader Abdurahman Abdullahi said.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Agriculture had extended financial and
technical support to the various states to enable them to
effectively dealt with the army worm invasion.
</P>
<P>
Since sufficient preparations were made, the army worm had not
inflicted heavy damage on crops in the country, Abdurahman said.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the army worm invasion had occurred in
most East African countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
