<DOCNO> XIE19990709.0019 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> OAU Chief Urges Africans to Meet Challenges Ahead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Secretary-General of the
Organization of African Unity (OAU), Salim Ahmed Salim, Thursday
urged African people to rise up against the "daunting challenges
of the peace and security" in the coming century.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the opening ceremony of OAU's 70th ordinary session
of the Council of Ministers in Algerian capital Algiers, Salim
said that the OAU meeting is held at the turning of the century
when the continent is facing daunting challenges in the
socio-economic and political fields and in a context of a rapidly
changing world.
</P>
<P>
There is increasing concerns on whether Africa can succeed in
putting its house in order and enter the new millenium better
prepared for peace and development and assume the right position
in the world, said the OAU chief.
</P>
<P>
In a continent plagued by political instability and conflicts,
both domestic and regional, the OAU meeting will discuss first of
all the political issues like the peace and stability in the
Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC), the border dispute between
Ethiopia and Eritrea, and some other conflicts in such countries
as Angola and Somalia.
</P>
<P>
Despite the determined efforts at various levels, Salim said,
conflicts continue to rage in the continent.
</P>
<P>
These conflicts, whether internal or inter-state, he said, have
caused considerable loss of life, imposed immense suffering on the
people and destroyed valuable infrastructures.
</P>
<P>
Refugees and displaced people, a by-product of armed conflicts
and instability, will also be discussed at the OAU meetings.
</P>
<P>
On the socio-economic front, African people are still suffering
from poverty, illiteracy, diseases, including pandemics such as
HIV/AIDS and malaria, afflict an increasing segment of the
population, he said.
</P>
<P>
Debt, which has piled up to 370 billion U.S. dollars, is
draining off African people's effort for socio-economic recovery,
Salim pointed out.
</P>
<P>
The ministers will examine the specific recommendations and
proposals from a special contact group to negotiate with creditor
nations and organizations for debt relief.
</P>
<P>
Insecurity and instability also effectively undermine efforts
at economic and social transformation, he said.
</P>
<P>
To meet the challenges of peace and development, "development
through cooperation and economic integration should be considered
in the context of the challenge of peace, security and stability,"
Salim said.
</P>
<P>
The OAU was founded on June 25 of 1963 to promote unity and
solidarity among independent African countries. It had 32 members
when established and now has 53 member states. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
