<HEADLINE> Cipollini Takes Second Stage Win at Tour de France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Italian Mario Cipollini scored his
back-to-back win in the Tour de France as he led the fifth stage
on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The sprinting ace edged Germany's Erik Zabel to win the fourth
stage of the Tour de France in a photo finish on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Belgian Tom Steels, who won two stages earlier in the week,
came in second, just clear of Tour leader Jaan Kirsipuu, who took
Sunday's first sprint finish at Challans.
</P>
<P>
Kirsipuu's placing earned a time deduction of eight seconds to
maintain the Estonian's overall lead over Steels.
</P>
<P>
The race's fifth stage was one of the longest of the Tour, 233.
5 kilometers from Bonneval to Amiens in the Picardy region.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
