<HEADLINE> Baker Shatters Women's European Breaststroke Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Britain's Zoe Baker broke the
European long-course women's 50 meters breaststroke record with a
time of 31.52 seconds at the national swimming championships at
Sheffield on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Baker beat the previous time of 31.58 set by East Germany's
Silke Hoerner in the first 50 meters of the 100 meters
breaststroke at the 1988 Seoul Olympics.
</P>
<P>
The Sheffield championships are doubling as trials for this
month's European championships in Istanbul. 
</P>
</TEXT>
