<HEADLINE> UK Post Office To Become Public Company </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Britain's Royal Mail, the Post
Office, is to be converted into a public limited company, with the
government owning its shares.
</P>
<P>
Trade and Industry Secretary Stephen Byers told MPs in a White
Paper the Royal Mail's monopoly on letter deliveries would be
reduced in return for more commercial freedoms.
</P>
<P>
The move would honor Labor's manifesto commitment to give the
state organization greater commercial freedom, the Secretary said.
</P>
<P>
Under the proposals, the Government will continue to own all
the shares in the Organizatiion, a move designed to reassure trade
unions that there are no plans to privatize the service.
</P>
<P>
"We intend to provide commercial freedom while maintaining the
Post Office in public ownership," Byers said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
