<HEADLINE> Thailand, Malaysia Promote Border Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Thai and Malaysian tourism
businesses have agreed to cooperate in promoting tourism in the
border areas of the two neighboring countries, according to a
report by Thailand News Agency on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Executives of tourism businesses of the two countries have set
up a joint committee to seek ways to promote tourism in three
southern provinces of Thailand and five Malaysian states, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
The bilateral cooperation would also enhance the development of
tourism industry in a regional growth area, called the
Indonesia-Malaysia-Thailand Growth Triangle, established by the
three neighboring members of the Association of Southeast Asian
Nations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
