<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UK Bank Keeps Interest Rates Unchanged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of England's Monetary
Policy Committee on Thursday left Britain's key short-term
interest rate unchanged at 5.00 percent.
</P>
<P>
The decision was widely expected, as the Bank has already cut
base rates seven times in the last nine months to boost the
economy.
</P>
<P>
Last month the Bank reduced base rates by a quarter point to a
22-year low. Since then there have been clear signs of economic
recovery.
</P>
<P>
The stock market and the pound were lower after the Bank's
decision. The pound has continued to weaken against the dollar
after U.S. interest rates were raised, falling to a three-year low
of 1.5542 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Bank's decision was welcomed by business leaders. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
