<DOCNO> XIE19990709.0044 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rwandan Foreign Minister Sacked </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Rwandan President Pasteur Bizimungu
fired the country's Foreign Minister Amri Sued Ismail in a
surprising move Wednesday, the Rwanda News Agency reported
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
A senior Rwandan government official who requested not to be
named said that Ismail was not defending the interests of the
country in his declarations to the media and foreigners.
</P>
<P>
"He is also charged with embezzlement," the official was quoted
as saying. "As Ambassador to Egypt before becoming Foreign Affairs
Minister, he was using his position to force his successor to
continue to pay his salary, and rent to his wife who stayed in
Cairo."
</P>
<P>
Ismail was appointed to the foreign affairs portfolio in
February 1999 following an overwhelming cabinet reshuffle.
</P>
<P>
He had been heading the Rwandan delegation that was negotiating
peace in the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) before he was
called back to Kigali late last week.
</P>
<P>
He was replaced by Augustin Iyamuremye who was serving as
Information Minister.
</P>
<P>
Ismail's sacking occurred as he was preparing to leave for
Algerian capital Algiers, to participate to the Organization of
African Unity (OAU) summit.
</P>
<P>
Official sources from the President's office said that the
firing of Ismail will not change Rwanda's stand on the DRC issue
and will not harm the signing of a peaceful agreement.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
