<HEADLINE> Ghana's Asutifi district records 178 Buruli cases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
 NAIROBI, July 8 (Xinhua) -- One hundred and seventy-eight
cases of Buruli ulcer have been recorded in the Asutifi district
in Ghana's Brong Ahafo region, the Ghana News Agency reported
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
 Mr Stephen Anane, Asutifi District Diseases Control Officer,
told the reporters Wednesday at Kenyasi that out of the number,
eight have been referred to the Komfo Anokye and Sunyani hospitals
while ten victims have recovered.
</P>
<P>
 Most of the reported victims are said to be school children.
</P>
<P>
 Mr Anane said the disease is endemic in three of the six
sub-districts of the district. These are Dadiesoaba, Hwidiem and
Acherensua.
</P>
<P>
 He said most of the victims are finding it difficult to
travel to the sub-district headquarters for treatment due to
financial constraints.
</P>
<P>
 He, therefore, suggested the establishment of treatment camps
in the endemic communities to treat the victims.
</P>
<P>
 The Brong Ahafo Regional Health Management Team and Action
Aid, an NGO,
</P>
<P>
have provided the District Health Management Team with dressing
materials.
</P>
<P>
 Mr Anane commended Mr Hyiaman Asante Amoako, Asutifi District
Chief Executive, and the District Assembly for providing one
million cedis (about 432 U.S. dollars) to supplement the DHMT's
efforts in combating the disease. 
</P>
</TEXT>
