<HEADLINE> Stocks End Mixed On Wall Street </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stocks ended mixed
Thursday with the Dow Jones industrial average falling and the
Nasdaq index rising.
</P>
<P>
The Dow index closed down 60.47 at 11,126.89 on profit taking
after strong second-quarter profit forecasts have pushed the blue
chip index to the record high. General Electric's stock, a Dow
component, moved lower as investors locked in their profits from
the previous gains.
</P>
<P>
The technology heavy Nasdaq composite index rose 28.82 at
2,771.86, surpassing the record closing high of 2,743.04 set
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The index was pushed higher by a wide array of technology
shares. Yahoo! rose after its second-quarter earning in a report
topped expectation while Computer maker Apple was higher as
BancBoston upgraded its outlook on the stock.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index fell 1.44 at 1,394.42. The NYSE
composite index fell 2.42 at 654.05.
</P>
<P>
The American Stock Exchange index rose 6.55 at 808.69 and the
Russell 2000 index of smaller companies rose 2.06 at 454.75.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues outnumbered advancers by a 4-to-3 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,654 down, 1,293 up and 614
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume increased to 820.02 million shares from 776.84
million in the previous session. 
