<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 90 Million Chinese Join Pension Security Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 9 (Xinhua) -- By the end of this June, 91.2
million in-service employees in China have been listed under a
national pension security program, an increase of 6.44 million
over the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Zuoji, Minister of Labor and Social Security, disclosed
the figures in a report to today's hearing on the issue of state
factory layoffs by the Financial and Economic Committee of the
National People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
By the end of this June, the country's pension security funds
have raised 72.5 billion yuan (8.7 billion US dollars), up 10.1
billion yuan, while the collection rate of the pension security
reached 87.1 percent, up 4.4 percentage points.
</P>
<P>
In the first half of the year, 99 percent of pension-holders
got paid, with the distribution of 296 million yuan delayed, of
which, 200 million yuan has been paid so far.
</P>
<P>
The official disclosed that while trying to make timely and
efficient payment of pension, the governments at different levels
have also made more than five billion yuan due payment to
pensioners.
</P>
<P>
Currently, the country's social security programs mostly cover
state-owned factories.
</P>
<P>
Zhang urged to expand the coverage of social security programs
and said efforts should be made to include overseas-funded
companies, collectively-owned firms and private industries in the
programs.
</P>
<P>
He also called for stricter control over the pension security
funds and stopping the misuse of the funds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
