<HEADLINE> Shenzhen Provides Best Air in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Shenzhen, the south China economic
powerhouse opposite Hong Kong, has provided the best air for
Chinese city dwellers over the past week.
</P>
<P>
From July 2-8, the city's air pollution index was only 13,
according to a weekly report by the China Environment Monitoring
Center. It was followed by Zhuhai, a city opposite Macao, and
Beihai, a coastal city in Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The weekly report on air quality in 46 major Chinese cities,
issued here today, said that widespread rainfalls over the past
week has helped improve air qualities in most northern cities
compared with the previous week, and most Chinese cities reported
fairly good air quality.
</P>
<P>
Slight air pollution was reported in Beijing, whose air
pollution index was 114 last week, Urumqi, 116, Jinan, 116, and
Tianjin, 102. All four are located in the northern part of the
country.
</P>
<P>
Besides the three cleanest cities, ten more including Xiamen
and Guilin reported excellent air quality, while 29 cities
including inland ones like Shenyang, Taiyuan and Xi'an, and
coastal ones like Shanghai, Qingdao and Fuzhou reported good air
quality.
</P>
<P>
Suspended articles have been the main pollutants in most
northern cities, including Beijing.  
</P>
</TEXT>
