<HEADLINE> Symposium Targets Reform of China's Tax, Fee Systems </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, July 9 (Xinhua) -- An international symposium on China'
s reform of tax and fee systems ended today in the capital city of
northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The five day event was organized by the State Administration of
Taxation, the United Nations Development Program (UNDP) and the
International Monetary Fund (IMF).
</P>
<P>
"China's reform on tax and fee systems should be focused on
solving the problem of unreasonable charges, which have
aggravated the burden on enterprises and residents and caused
losses of state revenues and weakened the macro-control capacity
of the government," said Mi Jianguo from the Development Research
Center of the State Council.
</P>
<P>
Unreasonable fees mainly refer to those charged by local
governmental departments of different levels without obeying
central regulations.
</P>
<P>
Government officials and scholars probed the necessity and task
of China's reform of tax and fee systems and carried out wide
exchanges on their views at the symposium, sources said.
</P>
