<HEADLINE> EU Lifts Ban On British Beef Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission has
proposed a conditional lifting of a three-year ban on British beef
exports from August 1, a spokesman said here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The decision is expected to end a worldwide embargo on British
beef sales which is said to have cost Britain's farming industry
about two billion U.S. dollars in lost sales.
</P>
<P>
But the EU executive Thursday extended a ban on Portuguese beef
exports because of fears of transmitting mad cow disease. The ban
will not be lifted until August 2000. The decision has been
slammed by the Portuguese government.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman for the European Union's Standing Veterinary
Committee said the date for lifting the British beef ban was set
under the Date-Based Export Scheme. 
</P>
