<HEADLINE> Top Lawmaker Calls for Greater Care of Layoffs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Strong efforts should be made to
ensure the needs of workers laid off by state-owned enterprises,
and the process of finding new jobs for them is a priority.
</P>
<P>
The call for action was made by Li Peng, Chairman of the
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC) who
stressed that China is a socialist country with its people the
masters.
</P>
<P>
