party committees and governments at different levels should take
note of the plight of laid off workers," said Li today at a
meeting of the NPC Financial and Economic Committee to hear
reports by relevant State Council departments on the issue of
factory layoffs.
</P>
<P>
Li emphasized that the NPC should supervise the government as
well as the supreme court and the supreme procuratorate with its
power endorsed by the Constitution.
</P>
<P>
"The issue of state factory layoffs is one that has drawn
attention from the whole society and is related to the interests
of workers as well as the general situation of the reform,
development and stability," the top lawmaker noted.
</P>
<P>
He acknowledged that to deal with the issue of factory layoffs
is a long term task, adding that it can only be done through the
joint efforts of the whole society.
