<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The Round-the-Silk-Road
international Road Cyclings will shift to Beijing from July 21 to
24 with cyclists from 14 countries and regions participating,
organisers said here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The annual road cycling event was initiated in 1992 and has
been alternated between Beijing, Gansu province and Xinjiang Uygur
Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The four-day tournament, titled the '99 Tour-de-China
International Road Cycling Race, was aimed to celebrate the
fiftieth anniversary of the People's Repulic of China and promote
Chinese bid for 2008 Olympics, said organisers.
</P>
<P>
The race, which spans a total of 673.6 kilometers of four
stages including one prologue, is also one of the biggest race in
Asia this year. 
</P>
