<HEADLINE> Al-Itihad Senior Official Assassinated in Somali </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The funeral of the assassinated
Colonel Abdullahi Irad took place Friday in south Mogadishu where
many officials from his organization, the Islamic fundamentalist
group known as Al-Itihad Al-Islam, paid him the last respect.
</P>
<P>
Irad, head of the operations for the Al-Itihad Al-Islam, was
killed in south Mogadishu late Thursday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Eyewitnesses said the official, whose organization is based in
Zone Five, was attacked by about four gunmen riding a taxi outside
a mosque in Towfiq quarter of south Mogadishu controlled by
faction leader Hussein Mohamed Aidid.
</P>
<P>
Eyewitnesses said the gunmen had been wandering around quite a
while before identifying their target.
</P>
<P>
Relatives said Irad was hit by four bullets in the chest and
died in Mogadishu Private hospital Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
Irad's relatives claimed that he was assassinated by Ethiopian
manipulated Somali gunmen, and that he has been having problems
lately with the Ethiopians who had recently been influencing some
Somali factions and what they called unknown missionaries working
inside the capital.
</P>
<P>
The Al-Itihad Al-Islam of Ethiopia who call themselves "West
Somali Liberation Front" claim that they are fighting to liberate
Zone Five from the regime of Ethiopia.  
</P>
</TEXT>
