<HEADLINE> China, Kazakhstan to Promote Trade Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Chinese foreign trade minister Shi
Guangsheng, in a meeting today with Kazakh Deputy Prime Minister
and Foreign Minister Kasymzhomart Tokayev, said that the two
countries, whose economies are mutually complementary, can enhance
economic and trade ties by promoting cooperation between their
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Shi, minister of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation, said
he believes that Tokayev's current China visit will play an
important role in furthering bilateral economic and trade ties.
</P>
<P>
Tokayev said that the two countries' economic and trade
relations are enjoying smooth development and that Kazakhstan is
ready to expand its economic and trade cooperation with China.
</P>
<P>
He said that there exist great potentials for bilateral
cooperation in the power industry, railway transportation and
other sectors.
</P>
<P>
After the meeting, Shi and Tokayev signed a framework agreement
on China providing preferential loans to Kazakhstan.
</P>
<P>
It is learned that trade volume between the two countries stood
at 375 million U.S. dollars in the first five months of this year,
an increase of 107.2 percent over the corresponding period of last
year.
</P>
<P>
China mainly exports food, daily necessities and household
appliances to Kazakhstan, while Kazakhstan exports nonferrous
metal, steel and wool to China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
