<HEADLINE> Spaniard Costa Strolls to Semi-finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Spainish Albert Costa showed his
flair at high-altitude events as he drubbed Vince Spadea in
straight sets at the quarterfinals of the 550,000 U.S. dollars
Swiss Open.
</P>
<P>
Costa, seeded eighth, lived up to his reputation as the King of
Mountains, cruised to a 6-3, 6-2 win over Spadea, ranked 29, the
sole member of the Top 30 who is yet to win a tournament title.
</P>
<P>
Costa has done well at high-altitude events including winning
the title in the 1,050-meter-high GStaad clay here in 1996 and
twice taking the trophy at Kitzbuhel, Austria, the other summer
alpine event on the ATP Tour.
</P>
<P>
World No. 28 Costa will meet Saturday either sixth-seeded
compatriot Francisco Clavet or Moroccan surprise Younes El Aynaoui,
who claimed third seed Marcelo Rios as a second-round upset victim.
</P>
<P>
Costa has won all of his nine career titles on clay with the
last triumph coming in April in Estoril. 
</P>
