<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks Close Weaker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The Australian sharemarket Friday
slumped almost 1.5 percent with falls across the board.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark all ordinaries index tumbled 45.3 points to
3,041, finishing near its intra-day low of 3,040 points.
</P>
<P>
On the local bourse, the all industrials index tumbled 86.5
points to 5,243.1, while the all resources dipped 9.6 points to
1,324.
</P>
<P>
Among industrials, banking stocks were among the hardest hit
Friday, with the industry sub-index slumping 103.8 points to
6,367.5.
</P>
<P>
The National Australia Bank offloaded 44 cents to 24.15
Australian dollars, ANZ surrendered 29 cents to 10.95 Australian
dollars, Westpac shed 18.1 cents to 9.65 Australian dollars and
Commonwealth Bank dropped 31 cents to 23.54 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
National turnover was 494.61 million stocks traded for 1.52
billion Australian dollars (1 billion U.S. dollars), with falling
stocks outnumbering rising ones by 684 to 589 and 436 stocks
remaining steady. 
