<HEADLINE> Malaysian Foreign Minister to Visit Singapore </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Foreign Minister Syed
Hamid Albar will arrive here next Monday for a two-day official
visit at the invitation of his Singapore counterpart, Shunmugam
Jayakumar, the Singapore Ministry of Foreign Affairs said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said in a press statement that this will be Syed
Hamid's introductory visit to Singapore as foreign minister and he
will be accompanied by his wife and a number of senior Malaysian
officials.
</P>
<P>
During his two-day stay in Singapore, Syed Hamid will meet with
Jayakumar and call on Singapore Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong, it
said.
</P>
<P>
Analysts here believe that the visit, the first by a Malaysian
foreign minister in at least more than a year, will be beneficial
to the improvement of the relations between the two neighbors.
</P>
<P>
Singapore and Malaysia are bound by a multiplicity of complex
ties and their relations have seen many ups and downs.
</P>
<P>
In recent years the two sides have run into a rough patch with
quite a number of issues including those over the relocation of
Malaysian Check-Point of Immigration and Quarantine facilities at
Tanjong Pagar Railway Station, the long-term water supply by
Malaysia to Singapore and the withdrawal of West Malaysian Central
Provident Fund.
</P>
<P>
The prime ministers of the two countries have agreed to solve
various bilateral problems within an overall package and
negotiations on the package started earlier this year. 
</P>
