<HEADLINE> India Evicts Intruders From Sub-Sector of Kashmir </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The Indian Armed Forces Friday
claimed to have cleared all intruders from the Batalik sub-sector
of Kashmir after a fierce battle and the army was on the Line of
Control (LOC) between India and Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
"The last of the intruders in Batalik sub-sector had been
kicked out and we are on the LOC in this entire sub-sector," Press
Trust of India (PTI) quoted Lt. Gen. Krishan Pal, who is in charge
of the entire Kargil operations, as saying Friday.
</P>
<P>
The process of pushing the intruders out of Drass and Mushkoh
sub-sectors were continuing and "it is a matter of time before the
intruders are thrown out of these areas, where small pockets are
still with them," he said. He added that the army had intensified
operations to evict what he called remaining Pakistan intruders in
these areas.
</P>
<P>
India launched a big military operation on May 8 to "flush out
infiltrators" from its side of the LOC and the fighting is still
going on.
</P>
<P>
According to reports reaching here from Islamabad, Pakistan
Friday decided to appeal to the Mujahideens fighting the Indian
Army to "help resolve the Kargil situation." The decision was
taken at the Pakistani cabinet's Defense Committee, the highest
decision-making body on security affairs in Pakistan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
