<HEADLINE> Chinese FM Meets with Japanese FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Both China's and Japan's foreign
ministers spoke highly of the high level talks and meetings
between the leaders of their two countries during Japanese Prime
Minister Keizo Obuchi's current China visit.
</P>
<P>
Tang Jiaxuan told his Japanese counterpart Masahiko Komura that
the leaders had confirmed the significance of the establishment of
a friendly and cooperative partnership which is devoted to peace
and development, especially as this had been achieved in the light
of historical lessons to help both face the future positively.
</P>
<P>
"They had also agreed to speed up the implementation of a
series of important political consensus and cooperation agreements
reached last year," Tang added in his meeting with Komura.
</P>
<P>
