results and that it will help further understanding, consolidate
consensus, deepen cooperation and push forward bilateral ties to
develop in a sound and stable manner.
</P>
<P>
In response, Komura said that Chinese President Jiang Zemin's
Japan visit last Autumn indicated a new development phase in
bilateral relations, and Obuchi's current visit will further the
bilateral friendly and cooperative partnership which is devoted to
peace and development.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that the visit has achieved its goal of building
bridges for the development of Japan-China relations into the 21st
century," Komura added.  
