<HEADLINE> Visitors in Tour Groups to Macao Rise Sharply in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The number of visitors in tour groups
to Macao was 94,448 in May, up by 35.3 percent over the same month
of 1998, the latest official statistics show.
</P>
<P>
According to figures released Friday by the Macao Census and
Statistics Department, those coming from China's mainland areas
and Taiwan accounted for 83.4 percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
Visitors to Macao in tour groups in the first five months of
the year as a whole were 428,242, an increase of 16.8 percent over
the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, 6,954 Macao residents, out of a population
of some 430,000, traveled to other places in tour groups in May.
The figure rose 10.2 percent over the same month of 1998.
</P>
<P>
The most favored destinations of tour for Macao residents were
China's mainland areas (63.8 percent), Taiwan (9.2 percent) and
Thailand ( 7.1 percent).
</P>
<P>
During the first five months of this year, the number of Macao
residents traveled to other places in tour groups increased 16
percent over the same period of 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
