<HEADLINE> 30 Die of Gastroenteritis in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 9 (Xinhua) -- An outbreak of gastroenteritis
has claimed 30 lives in Nepal since mid-May, the official RSS news
agency said Friday.
</P>
<P>
About 16,000 others were affected by the disease, the RSS
quoted the Department of Health as saying.
</P>
<P>
Some 1,000 persons died of the disease last year, the news
agency said.
</P>
<P>
Due to poor hygienic conditions and the lack of safe drinking
water, Nepal is prone to various diseases, particularly in the
monsoon season which runs from June to September. 
