<HEADLINE> Shanghai Opens Telephone Line on Weather Information </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The meteorological bureau and post
office of this metropolis in east China opened a public telephone
line Thursday to provide local residents with information about
weather.
</P>
<P>
Just dial number 221, people in Shanghai will receive a variety
of detailed weather information from the seven branches of the
line.
</P>
<P>
The weather information available for residents include 24-
hour, rush-hour and whole-week weather forecast on the city's
urban and rural areas as well as weather forecast for world major
cities, domestic and overseas tourist sites and medical advice
under different climates.
</P>
<P>
