<HEADLINE> ICBC Improves Project Loan Appraisal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The Industrial and Commercial Bank
of China (ICBC) has established a complete set of standards and
procedures for evaluating loaning project in a bid to improve
credit qualities.
</P>
<P>
The ICBC sources said that in 1998, to support the central
government's policies of expanding infrastructure construction and
domestic demand, the bank completed appraisal of 1,683 loaning
projects, involving 165.6 billion yuan in total loans.
</P>
<P>
In December 1998, the ICBC established a bank-wide credit
appraisal committee, with 143 expert members from both the bank
and outside of the bank, aiming to improving the appraisal work.
</P>
<P>
Vice-President of the ICBC Tian Ruizhang said that, as a state-
owned commercial bank, the ICBC must foster the ability to
independently evaluate its loaning projects, selecting the right
clients while preventing repetitive construction.
</P>
<P>
He said that the ICBC should also improve its financial
services to promote the country's economic growth, at the same
time minimizing credit risks.
</P>
<P>
According to Tian, the ICBC will produce detailed procedures
and software systems for evaluating loaning projects in power
networks, highways, real estate development and other industries.
</P>
<P>
The repayment ability of the debtor and credit risks will be
the key factors in project appraisal, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
