<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Prime Minister Leaves for Libya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian Prime Minister Meles
Zenawi left here Friday Morning for Tripoli to pay a two-day
official visit to Libya.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian News Agency quoted the Ethiopian Foreign Ministry
as saying that Meles will discuss bilateral issues with Libyan
leader Muammar Gaddafi during his visit in Libya.
</P>
<P>
It was recalled that Libyan leader Gaddafi sent a special envoy
to Ethiopia in June this year, expressing its desire to enhance
bilateral relations with Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
The Libyan envoy also expressed his country's desire to
facilitate conditions for the implementation of the Organization
of African Unity (OAU) framework agreement for peace resolution of
Ethio-Eritrean border conflict during the visit here.
</P>
<P>
The envoy, who is African Affairs Secretary in the Libyan
Foreign Ministry, said Libya is ready to do everything possible
for the implementation of the OAU peace plan.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian News Agency reported that Meles will travel to
Algiers for the 35th OAU summit after his two-day stay in Tripoli.
</P>
<P>
The forthcoming 35th OAU summit will discuss various issues
including economic development, refugee affairs and security in
Africa, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
