<HEADLINE> Gold Price in Hong Kong Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The gold price in Hong Kong went
up 6 HK dollars to close at 2,379 HK dollars a tael on Friday,
according to Po Sang Bank, one of the major gold dealers in Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
The gold price is equivalent to 257,38 U.S. dollars a troy
ounce, 0.65 U.S. dollars up from the previous close at Friday's
exchange rate of one U.S. dollar against 7.7590 HK dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
