<HEADLINE> Zhu Holds Talks with Obuchi (6) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Zhu and Obuchi also discussed the bilateral negotiations on
China's entry into the World Trade Organization (WTO) that were
concluded by departments of both countries through joint efforts
during Obuchi's visit. Both sides have issued a joint press
communique on this.
</P>
<P>
The two prime ministers both expressed their satisfaction with
this and Zhu said he has noticed Obuchi's positive attitude
towards China's entry into the organization, adding that he
appreciates and is grateful for this.
</P>
<P>
Obuchi said he hopes China will joint the WTO this year.
</P>
<P>
They also discussed the present international situation and
regional issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the talks, Zhu presided over a welcoming ceremony for
Obuchi at the square in front of the Great Hall of the People.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan, Minister in Charge of
State Development Planning Commission Zeng Peiyan, Japanese Home
Affairs Minister Takeshi Noda, Foreign Minister Masahiko Komura,
and other senior officials of the two countries attended the talks.
</P>
