<HEADLINE> FIFA Selects All-Star Team for Women's World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
LOS ANGELES, July 8 (Xinhua) -- FIFA Technical Study Group
selected 16 players for the All-Star team of the 3rd women's World
Cup soccer tournament.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team have the most players on the list. They are
goal-keeper Gao Hong, strikers Sun Wen and Jin Yan, midfielders Liu
Ailing and Zhao Lihong, defenders Wang Liping and Wen Lirong.
</P>
<P>
The host team the United States have five players selected. They
are goal-keeper Briana Scurry, defender Carla Overbeck and Brandi
Chastain, midfielder Michelle Akers and striker Mia Hamm.
</P>
<P>
The All-Star team also include Doris Fitschen and Bettina Wiegmann
of Germany, Sissi of Brazil and Ann Kirstin Aarones of Norway.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time that FIFA selects an All-Star team for the
women's World Cup. 
</P>
</TEXT>
