<HEADLINE> AFC Makes Asian Olympic Qualifying Final Round Draw </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
LOS ANGELES, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Football Conferdation
(AFC) made the draw for the final round of the AFC Olympic
Qualifying Tournament here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The nine team final round will be divided into three groups with
top teams from each group qualify for the Olympic Games at Sydney in
2000.
</P>
<P>
Following are the draw for the final round:
</P>
<P>
Group 1:
</P>
<P>
Qatar or India, Saudi Arabia or China, Kuwait
</P>
<P>
Group 2:
</P>
<P>
South Korea, China or Iraq, Bahrain
</P>
<P>
Group 3:
</P>
<P>
Japan, Kazakhstan, Qatar or Thailand
</P>
<P>
The final placing of the teams will be confirmed when the first
stage of the tournament comes to an end on July 24. Three matches
in group 3 and 2 matches in group 9 are still to be played. 
</P>
</TEXT>
