<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary At 0830 GMT, July 9 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- The U.N. Security Council on Thursday evening
"warmly welcomed" a peace accord signed by Sierra Leone's warring
parties, saying that "the United Nations will have a key role to
play in the implementation of this agreement."
</P>
<P>
Voicing his welcome to the peace accord, U.N. secretary-general
Kofi Annan, who was on a visit to the West African nation, said
Thursday that the peace deal signed this week to end the civil war
in the country was an encouraging sign for peace across the whole
continent of Africa.(UN-Sierra Leone-Peace)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA -- More than 70 people were feared dead on
Thursday in a heavy fighting between the government forces and the
rebels near the country's capital of Bogota.
</P>
<P>
About 40 government soldiers and 37 Revolutionary Armed Forces
of Colombian guerrillas died in the battle that began at dawn
around the Andean village of Gutierrez, 15 miles (25 km) south of
Bogota, an army spokeswoman said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, another 96 troops were missing after they lost radio
contact with the rest of their company shortly after midday, she
added.(Colombia-Rebels-Fight)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BERLIN -- Germany started repatriating Kosovo Albanian refugees
on Thursday, local reports said.
</P>
<P>
The first group of 160 refugees were airlifted from the German
city of Munster to the Macedonian capital of Skopje, and then sent
to Kosovo by bus.
</P>
<P>
Germany accepted a total of 15,000 ethnic Albanian refugees
during the Kosovo War, the largest number taken in by any Western
country. In addition, Germany says there are another 180,000
Kosovo Albanians who have been living in the country and should
also return to their homeland. (Germany-Refugee)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- Eighteen people were injured as a train carrying
235 passengers hit a truck near Houston City in Texas Thursday,
reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
The eastbound Sunset Limited was traveling from Los Angeles,
California to Orlando of Florida when it hit the rig. Track was
torn up and two engines and seven cars were off to the side. (US-
Traffic-Accident) 
</P>
</TEXT>
