<HEADLINE> Uganda Cracks Down Armed Robberies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Uganda's security authority has
taken joint operations to crack down armed robberies that hit the
capital city Kampala in the past two weeks, a report here said
Friday.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the security agencies have recovered
documents detailing majority areas targeted in a wave of armed
robberies. Four sub- machine guns, three pistols and live
ammunition have been recovered in Kampala and Entebbe, a city
south of the Ugandan capital, in the joint operations in which 10
robbers have been killed and scores captured.
</P>
<P>
The operations were triggered off by the robbery of an
unspecified amount of money from the United Forex Bureau on
Kampala Road on June 26. A policeman was shot dead and a gun
taken in the incident.
</P>
<P>
A security source said the robbers' maps recovered had on major
shopping complexes, forex bureaus and entertainment centers in
Kampala, which might be their targets. 
</P>
