<HEADLINE> U.S. Businessman (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two pieces of Chinese pottery in Latham's office illustrate his
belief. Jingdezhen pottery can be found in the markets in the
Middle East or on shipwrecks in the Philippines. It is trade that
links different countries, he explained.
</P>
<P>
Chinese pottery made Jingdezhen, a small obscure city in
Jiangxi Province, famous. But, it is no longer the only thing that
links Jingdezhen with the rest of the world. Latham's company has
more than 20 joint ventures in China and one is in that city.
</P>
<P>
