in the past two decades, China has gone from a closed economy to
an open-trade one and its trade as a percentage of GDP exceeds
that of the U.S.
</P>
<P>
Latham said that his company believes that China is, "every day,
every week, every year," making progress towards establishing an
economy based on market forces and on clear laws and transparency,
so there are reasons for continuing to be optimistic.
</P>
<P>
He said China's strongest friends in the U.S. are American
companies, not because of the money involved -- not all companies
are profitable -- but because of that relations between countries
are always based on trade.  
