<HEADLINE> Kenya Seeks Oil Exploration Partner </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The Kenyan government will seek to
attract potential partners to assist with petroleum prospecting.
</P>
<P>
Kenyan Energy Minister Chris Okemo made the remarks Thursday
when addressing the launch of the Petroleum Institute of East
Africa in capital Nairobi, the East African Standard newspaper
reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Okemo said a lot of data had been collected and his government
had compiled documents to be used to attract interested partners.
</P>
