billion shillings (about 169 million U.S. dollars) in the
exploration of oil and gas over the past 15 years.
</P>
<P>
The ministry once said an area of about 300,000 square
kilometers in the country is considered suitable for oil and gas
exploration.
</P>
<P>
Okemo also urged oil industry players in the country to make
contributions to the proposed environment protection bill.
</P>
<P>
The newly-established institute should actively participate on
the National Spill Response Committee to ensure Kenya can
effectively handle disasters and prevent serious environmental
damage and loss of life and property, the minister added.
