<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Earns $879 Million in Foreign Currency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The National Bank of Ethiopia
has announced that a sum of 879 million U.S. dollars had been
earned in foreign currency during the just-ended 1998/99 fiscal
year ending on July 7.
</P>
<P>
Bank Governor Tekle-Wold Atnafu said the amount, earned from
foreign trade, foreign loans and private dealings, will make
substantial contributions to improve the country's foreign
currency reserve, the state-run Ethiopian Herald reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
This year's earning shows an increase of 72 million U.S.
dollars over that of the previous 1997/98 year, said Tekle-Wold.
</P>
<P>
Noting that the amount earned from foreign trade was 499.8
million U.S. dollars, the governor said this represented a fall of
17 percent from that of the previous year resulting from a decline
in coffee prices on the world market and reduced earnings from
hides and skin sector due to the financial crisis in Southeast
Asia.
</P>
<P>
A total of 1,448.5 million dollars had been disbursed for the
importation of goods during the 1998/99 year, which represented an
increase of 47 million dollars over the previous year, added the
governor. 
</P>
</TEXT>
