<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets With Kazakhstan's Deputy PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 9 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin, in a meeting
with Kazakhstan's Deputy Prime Minister Kasymzhomart Tokayev here
today, expressed confidence in developing ties with Kazakhstan and
said he is looking forward to a visit by Kazakh President
Nursultan Abishevich Nazarbayev to China this year.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that Kazakhstan is an important neighbor of China
and that the good-neighbor, friendly, mutually beneficial, and
cooperative ties between the two countries have had sound growth.
</P>
<P>
They have smoothly resolved whatever remaining border disputes
and the 1,700-km border of the two countries is legally defined as
a border without any problem, he said.
</P>
<P>
Tokayev, who is Kazakhstan's Foreign Minister, thanked Jiang
for the meeting and extended Nazarbayev's regards to Jiang, and
said that his country will further its efforts to develop ties
with China. With these good political relations, he said,
Kazakhstan shares similar views on international affairs to a
great degree with China and will continue its support for China's
principled stand against national divisiveness.  
</P>
</TEXT>
