<HEADLINE> Netherlands Halts Aid to Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Netherlands has stopped offering
more aid to Kenya, citing that there is no enabling environment
for it.
</P>
<P>
Kenya was not on the list of 17 developing countries passed
recently by the Dutch parliament to benefit from their aid, the
East African Standard newspaper reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Kees Rade, Charge d'Affairs at the Netherlands Embassy in
Nairobi, disclosed Thursday that his government will phase out
their aid programs which amounted to 1.5 billion shillings (about
20.8 million U.S. dollars) in 1998 over a four-year period.
</P>
<P>
Corruption scandals, land grabbing, unbudgeted spending of
public resources and slow privatization are some of the reasons
given for the halt of aid to the east African country, said Rade.
</P>
</TEXT>
