<HEADLINE> Zambia Arrests 135 Suspected Drug Traffickers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, July 9 (Xinhua) -- At least 135 suspected drug peddlers
have been arrested by Zambian Drug Enforcement Commission (DEC)
within one month.
</P>
<P>
Of the 135 suspects, 119 were Zambians, and the others are from
Tanzania, Italy, Angola, Mozambique and Democratic Republic of
Congo. They were arrested last month with a number of narcotic
drugs and psychotropic substances worth 395 million kwacha (about
160,000 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Times of Zambia newspaper Friday quoted DEC acting chief
investigation officer and spokesman Nason Banda as saying that 105
of the suspects have already been prosecuted.
</P>
<P>
Banda said Thursday that the commission has since seized drugs
include cannabis, heroin, diazepam, phenobarbitone, morphine and
miraa.
</P>
<P>
The commission would not rest until it rids the country of
drugs, he pledged.
</P>
<P>
He also warned would-be drug peddlers of severe punitive.
</P>
