<HEADLINE> Cyprus Stock Market Weekly Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The Cyprus stock market extended
its mounting pace this week, a weekly market review said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The review, issued by the Cyprus Investment and Securities
Corporation Limited (CISCO), said volume of transactions
fluctuated in close coordination with the CISCO Index and was
generally sustained at high levels ranging between 13-19 million
Cyprus pounds (26-38 million U.S. dollars) daily.
</P>
<P>
The CISCO All-Share Index hit a new record high on July 5, 1999
at 848.9 points. Volume of transactions also peaked for the week
on the same day at 18.7 million pounds (37.4 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
For the following two trading sessions, the market briefly
reversed its course and lost ground of 24.3 points, or 2.9
percent, as a result of profit-taking.
</P>
<P>
The CISCO All-Share Index was set on an ascending mode again on
July 8 when it closed at 832.5 points with a marginal weekly
ascent of 2.4 points. At this point the market registers a capital
appreciation estimated at 83.3 percent since the beginning of 1999.
</P>
<P>
The total volume of transactions in four trading sessions of
this week reached 73.4 million pounds (146.8 million dollars),
compared with 73.0 million pounds (146.0 million dollars) in five
trading days last week.
</P>
<P>
The average daily volume rose to 18.3 million pounds (36.6
million dollars), from 14.6 million pounds (25.2 million dollars)
the previous week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
