<HEADLINE> Sino-Japanese Joint Press Communique On WTO (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The two sides recognize that in order to inform the WTO
Secretariat of the conclusion of all bilateral negotiations
between China and Japan, they still have to complete the requisite
technical checks. The two sides agree to complete this work as
soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
2. Both sides believe that China's access to the WTO not only
is in the common interests of China and Japan, but also in the
interests of all WTO members.
</P>
<P>
The two sides reiterate that they are determined to continue
their close cooperation in the work group talks in Geneva to
realize the goal of China's entry into the WTO at the earliest
date.
</P>
<P>
3. Japan has consistently supported China's entry into the WTO
and the Chinese side appreciates this.
</P>
<P>
4. The two sides believe that the conclusion of all bilateral
negotiations will further strengthen the long-term, stable
economic relations between China and Japan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
