<HEADLINE> Asia Threatens to Boycott 2002 World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
LOS ANGELES, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Football Conferdation
(AFC) threatened to boycott the 2002 World Cup finals if FIFA fails
to meet their request of giving them a fifth qualifying spot.
</P>
<P>
After a special meeting of the AFC executive committee here on
Thursday, the AFC decided to boycott the 2002 World Cup if the FIFA
Extraordinary Congress fails to give Asia the fifth spot in the
World Cup finals, according to an AFC official.
</P>
<P>
FIFA has previously announced that Asia had a chance of getting
a fifth spot in the World Cup if the third-place finishers of the
Asian qualifying tournament win a playoff against the 14th placed
team in the European qualifying zone.
</P>
<P>
But the AFC insisted that they want a full spot, not a half, in
the World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
Yet the AFC decided that the boycott would not include Japan and
South Korea, co-hosts of the 2002 World Cup finals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
