<HEADLINE> Singapore, Croatia Sign Air Services Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Singapore and Croatia signed
Friday an air services agreement to formalize bilateral air
relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, each country can designate any number of
carriers to operate air services on any route between Singapore
and Croatia and beyond.
</P>
<P>
The air services agreement provides a framework for the
respective flag carriers to establish air linkages between the two
countries, the Singapore government said in a press release.
</P>
<P>
Currently, 63 airlines link Singapore directly to 123 cities
with over 3,100 weekly scheduled flights. 
</P>
