<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Seafood Exports Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam earned 410.3 million U.S.
dollars from exports of seafood in the first half of this year,
registering a year-on-year increase of eight percent, according to
a report of Vietnam's official news agency VNA.
</P>
<P>
Localities attaining high export value included Vietnam's
southern provinces of Ca Mau (61.82 million dollars), Soc Trang
(54 million dollars), Can Tho (35 million dollars), Ho Chi Minh
City (33 million dollars), Bac Lieu (26 million dollars), and
Khanh Hoa (24.5 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
Vietnam has made great efforts to boost seafood export. The
Ministry of Fisheries held a conference on seafood quality early
this year and created favorable conditions for enterprises to
participate in international fisheries fairs in Boston and
Brussels in March and April respectively. The ministry also
organized a fisheries fair in Ho Chi Minh City in February to
create opportunity for domestic and foreign businesses to seek
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
However, the figure of Vietnam's seafood-export turnover in the
first half of the year represented only 43 percent of this year's
fisheries plan.
</P>
<P>
High cost of materials (marine products) and low
competitiveness of exports in the world market, strict quality
requirements of the EU countries and limited capability in
processing high-quality products are reasons behind the low
accomplishment of the yearly plan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990709.0245 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South China Province to Spur Scientific Innovation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The government of south China's
Guangdong Province will spend one billion yuan on its scientific
innovation undertakings in three years.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, the scheme will also have a
financial support of 10 billion yuan from enterprises and the
special scientific and technological risk fund.
</P>
<P>
Under the program, the province will select and publish a list
of 100 scientific innovation projects annually which will enjoy
preferential treatment and receive major financial aid from the
provincial government.
</P>
<P>
Through the implementation of the program, the province will be
blessed with a strong contingent of senior scientists and
technicians and business executives, as well as the establishment
of 100 well-equipped research and development centers.
</P>
<P>
The program is expected to bring about more than 100 billion
yuan in economic returns and social benefits.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong recently selected 211 best new products as a result
of the scientific and technological innovations in the province,
and these products have brought to the province an extra 2.06
billion yuan in pre-tax profits every year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
