<HEADLINE> Indonesia Approves 54 Investment Projects in Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian government approved
54 investment projects in the tourism sector in the first five
months of 1999, The Business News bulletin reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The projects composed 47 foreign investment projects worth
about 91.02 million U.S. dollars and seven domestic investment
projects worth approximately 155.82 billion rupiah (11.26 million
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
According to data presented by the Ministry of Tourism, Art and
Cultural Affairs, of the 47 foreign investment projects, 28
projects worth 85.72 million U.S. dollars are found in the
construction and operation of new hotels.
</P>
<P>
The seven domestic investment projects approved by the
government are focused on the construction and operation of new
hotels.
</P>
<P>
The 54 foreign and domestic investment projects are expected to
create jobs for 3,540 Indonesian employees and 238 expatriates,
the bulletin said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
