<HEADLINE> South China Province Exports More Bicycles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 9 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong Province
exported 4.73 million bicycles in the first five months of the
year, earning 188 million U.S. dollars, up 26 percent and nine
percent respectively from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Dubbed as "kingdom of bicycles", China enjoys the reputation in
producing qualtiy bicycles.
</P>
<P>
But the country suffered setbacks in the export of bicycles
since the later half of 1997 due to the adverse impact of the
Asian financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong exported 8.65 million bicycles in 1998, with the
monthly export figure standing at 500,000 bicycles in the later
half of the past year.
</P>
<P>
Industry experts predict that in the later half of this year,
the province's export will continue to rise thanks to the improved
macro external environment.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, China has also raised tax rebate rate for
export of bicycles from 11 percent to 17 percent since January of
this year and the move has been proved good.  
</P>
</TEXT>
