<HEADLINE> Forest Fire Put Out In Inner Mongolia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 9 (Xinhua)-- A ferocious forest fire has been put
out in the Greater Hinggan Mountains in North China's Inner
Mongolia Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
According to a leading ranger of the region, the fire broke out
during July 1-3 in four virgin forest sites due to strong
thunderbolts.
</P>
<P>
The prolonged dry spell was blamed for the disaster.
</P>
<P>
Fires were extinguished on July 6 and some several thousand
rangers and forest workers are still checking for possible dangers.
</P>
<P>
The ranger said that weathermen have forecast rain in the
coming few days, which will be helpful in consolidating the fire
extinguishing work. 
</P>
</TEXT>
