<HEADLINE> Nicaragua Gets 200 Million Dollars in Remittance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, July 8 (Xinhua)-- Nicaragua earned last year 200
million dollars from foreign remittance inflows, rather than 800
million dollars announced by the Economic Commission for Latin
America (CEPAL), said Central Bank President Noe Ramirez on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Ramirez noted that 60 percent of the remittances came from the
United States and 40 percent Costa Rica.
</P>
<P>
The president described the remittances as a "blessing" for the
country as they went to the poorest of the society, relieving the
government from the burden of social spending.
</P>
<P>
Currently, there are about 450,000 Nicaraguans living in the
United States and 300,000 in Costa Rica, Nicaraguan authorities
said. 
</P>
