<HEADLINE> Mexican Economy to Grow 3 Percent This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Mexico's gross domestic product
(GDP) will increase by 3 percent in 1999, analysts of the
Financial Group Banamex-Accival said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The experts said the figures was obtained from the encouraging
growth of the macro-economy in the first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
They said Mexico's economy will surge more rapidly due to the
sound economic situation in the United States, which will permit
more Mexican exports to its northern neighbor.
</P>
<P>
In the first half of the year, Mexico's exports rose 10 percent,
especially in the manufacturing section.
</P>
<P>
Investment will also remain dynamic in the second half of the
year and surge by 6.2 percent, they said.
</P>
<P>
However, the annual inflation rate will reach 14 percent, they
added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
