<HEADLINE> Highlights of Major Beijing-Based Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Following are the highlights of
today's major Beijing-based newspapers:
</P>
<P>
 "People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- Jiang Zemin, Chinese president and chairman of the Central
Military Commission, attended a national conference on the
political work in the Chinese armed forces in Beijing yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, who is also general secretary of the Communist Party of
China Central Committee, is reported to have made an important
address to the conference.
</P>
<P>
The conference began on Monday and most of the participants are
ranking political commissars from the People's Liberation Army and
the Chinese People's Armed Police.
</P>
<P>
-- Japanese Prime Minister Keizo Obuchi arrived in Beijing by
special plane yesterday afternoon on an official visit to China as
guest of Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji.
</P>
<P>
This is Obuchi's first visit to China since he became prime
minister of Japan. His over-100-member entourage includes Home
Affairs Minister Takeshi Noda, Foreign Minister Masahiko Komura,
and other senior officials as well as people from the business
circle.
</P>
<P>
"Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- Vice-Premier Wen Jiabao has called on all of society to
appreciate the significance of protecting the ozone layer and
promoting international cooperation in environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks yesterday at a meeting of the organizing
committee for the 11th annual conference of the signatories of the
Montreal Protocol on Substances which Deplete the Ozone Layer to
be held in Beijing from November 29 to December 3 this year.
</P>
<P>
-- China yesterday demanded that the United States government
stick to its commitment that Tibet is a part of China and reject a
proposal by the House of Representatives to designate July 10 "
World Tibet Day."
</P>
<P>
Tibet is an inalienable part of Chinese territory and Tibetan
affairs are the internal affairs of China and no foreign country
has the right to interfere in them, said Foreign Ministry
spokeswoman Zhang Qiyue at a news conference here yesterday
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
 "China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- Creation of Sino-overseas commercial joint ventures is
expected to help promote China's commercial modernization, Chen
Bangzhu, vice-minister of the State Economic and Trade Commission
(SETC), said yesterday.
</P>
<P>
China hopes Sino-overseas commercial joint businesses will help
introduce advanced sales and management experise, and at the same
time increase the country's exports, Chen said.
</P>
<P>
-- Reduction and even an end to collecting a package of levies
on people and enterprises have been called for by the State
Development Planning Commission in a fresh bid to stimulate
domestic demand.
</P>
<P>
In a press release issued yesterday, the commission asked local
governments in a recent circular "to use the price lever to drive
domestic demand and promote the stable and steady development of
the national economy." 
</P>
</TEXT>
