<DOCNO> XIE19990709.0279 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippines Mayon Volcano Shows Weak Steaming Activity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Mayon Volcano has shown weak
steaming activity for the past 24 hours and seismic stations have
registered four high frequency volcanic earthquakes during the
period, the Philippine Institute of Volcanology and Seismology
(Phivolcs) said Friday.
</P>
<P>
In a press statement issued here, the Phivolcs said that its
experts recorded an emission rate of about 2,800 tons of sulfur
dioxide Thursday and a slight inflation in the southeast slope of
the volcano.
</P>
<P>
The volcano's overall condition stays at Alert Level 2, which
means the public should not venture inside the delineated
six-kilometer radius permanent danger zone and the seven-kilometer
safety buffer zone in the southeast sector, it said.
</P>
<P>
The institute said residents near the volcano's slopes should
be aware that gullies radiating out of Mayon, which is about 330
kilometers southeast of Manila, can easily serve as conduits for
loose volcanic debris that may be transported downslope.
</P>
<P>
The Phivolcs has noted since May 13 the ongoing activity of the
volcano, which is characterized by intermittent crater glow at the
summit area and a slight increase in sulfur dioxide emission.
</P>
<P>
On June 22, Mayon's mild eruption rained ash over surrounding
towns of the volcano.
</P>
<P>
Mayon's last major eruption on February 2, 1993 killed 78
people and affected 17,119 persons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990709.0280 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-09 </DATE_TIME>
