<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Three More Arrested for Faulty Expressway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Three project officials have been
arrested in central China's Henan province for severe dereliction
of duty which has resulted in a shoddy expressway culvert.
</P>
<P>
The three officials are project engineer Li Pengying, assistant
project supervisor Shi Haicheng and project supervising engineer
Guo Jinxing.
</P>
<P>
Prior to this, the police have apprehended three project
contractors who are directly responsible for the building of the
faulty culvert.
</P>
<P>
The provincial transport authorities received a report about
the shoddy culvert and discovered severe quality problems with the
expressway culvert, which was filled with rocks and bags of cement
instead of concrete.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has ordered the culvert be demolished
and reconstructed, and called up leading officials from ten other
key transportation projects to the site to learn a lesson from it.
</P>
<P>
China has increased quality inspections about engineering
projects nationwide since an improperly-built bridge collapsed in
the southwestern city of Chongqing earlier this year, killing 40.
</P>
<P>
Investigations show that the culvert project has been illegally
sub-contracted and the individual contractor used stone instead of
concrete to fill the culvert.
</P>
<P>
Due to severe dereliction of duty, the three project
supervisors failed to discover quality problems with the culvert
and resulted in an economic loss of 340,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
The Luosan expressway, extending 135 kilometers to link Luoyang
and Sanmenxia city, is listed as a key State project. Construction
of the 4.3-billion-yuan expressway started in early 1998 and is
expected to complete in 2002. 
</P>
</TEXT>
