<HEADLINE> 18 People Injured in U.S. Traffic Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Eighteen people were injured as
a train carrying 235 passengers hit a truck near Houston City in
Texas Thursday, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
The eastbound Sunset Limited was traveling from Los Angeles,
California to Orlando of Florida when it hit the rig. Track was
torn up and two engines and seven cars were off to the side.
</P>
<P>
Passengers said they heard the train's whistle blowing just
before the collision with the truck, which was pulling a salt
water tank. Some riders crawled through a window as smoke filled
the cars.
</P>
<P>
David Keith, administrator of the Rice Medical Center in Eagle
Lake, said most of the injured had bumps and bruises or were
suffering from heat exhaustion.
</P>
<P>
There were no warning lights or gates at the rural crossing
where the accident happened, about 100 kilometers west of Houston.
