<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 9 (Xinhua) -- A recent spot-check, conducted by
the State Quality and Technical Supervision Administration,
indicates that the quality of all the inspected air-conditioners
has reached the state quality standards.
</P>
<P>
The products were collected from 20 air-conditioner
manufacturers in eight provinces and municipalities including
Guangdong, Jiangsu, Zhejiang and Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Air-conditioners from these enterprises make up 80 percent of
the Chinese market, according to official statistics.
</P>
<P>
Aiming at a larger share of the rich air-conditioner market in
China, the enterprises have invested heavily to strengthen quality
control and develop new functions to cater to varying requirements
from consumers, said today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
Besides bringing down room temperatures during the sweltering
summer, some air conditioners can also filter the air in the house
and improve ventilation, to make staying indoors more comfortable
for residents.
</P>
<P>
However, compared to the enhanced performance of the air-
conditioners, the after-sales services provided by the air-
conditioner manufacturers remain far from satisfactory. 
