<HEADLINE> Big Hearted Shanghai Helps Tibet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The government of Shanghai
Municipality in east China today donated three million yuan worth
of aid materials to southwest China's Tibet Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The materials include medical instruments, medicines, motor
vehicles, television sets and study materials.
</P>
<P>
The donation is part of the city's large scale drive to help
Tibet, which includes 62 projects with a total of 94 million yuan
worth of cash or materials.
</P>
<P>
As one of the country's most developed areas, Shanghai is
active to help the economically less developed areas in China such
as Tibet.
</P>
<P>
Over the past four years, the city has sent 200 officials to
work in Tibet and invested 280 million yuan in a dozen projects
for the Shigatse Prefecture of Tibet including water supply
projects, a hospital to handle contagious diseases, a city square
and an exhibition center.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai's aid projects to the prefecture this year include
financial aid to 2,000 poor Tibetan students and the building of
ten rural hospitals, a radio and television station and an
archives exhibition hall.  
</P>
