<HEADLINE> Indonesia to Announce Poll Results on July 21: Election Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian Election Committee
(PPI) in its plenary meeting Thursday agreed the results of the
national vote count would be formalized on July 21.
</P>
<P>
"We are continuing to contact provincial committees that have
not submitted the results of their tally and tell them about the
documents they also have to send," PPI Chairman Jacob Tobing was
quoted by Antara News Agency Friday as saying.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian General Election Commission (KPU) originally
planned to announce the final June 7 election results on June 21,
but the announcement was delayed due to slow vote counting.
</P>
<P>
After a heated debate among its members, KPU at its plenary
meeting on July 1 decided to allow the PPI to begin the national
vote count on July 6.
</P>
<P>
The PPI has finished counting votes from a total of 14
provincial and six overseas committees.
</P>
<P>
According to the results of the PPI vote counting so far, the
Indonesian Democratic Party of Struggle (PDI-P) leads in eight
provinces, namely, Bali, Yogyakarta, Central Java, Lampung,
Central Kalimantan, East Kalimantan, South Sumatera and Jakarta.
</P>
<P>
The ruling Golkar Party meanwhile leads in Riau, Jambi, Irian
Jaya and East Timor.
</P>
<P>
The United Development Party (PPP) leads in Aceh and the
National Awakening Party (PKB) in East Java.
</P>
<P>
According to unofficial results collected by the official
Antara News Agency from the provincial chapters of PPI, up to
Friday morning, PDI-P remains in the lead with 35 million votes,
Golkar 22.7 million votes, PKB 13.2 million votes, PPP 10.9
million votes and the National Mandate Party (PAN) 7.3 million
votes.
</P>
<P>
A total of 117.8 million eligible voters were registered for
the June 7 general elections. 
</P>
</TEXT>
