<HEADLINE> Albanian President Stresses Regional Stability </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Albanian President Rexhep Mejdani
Thursday said that stability in the Balkan region closely linked
with its development.
</P>
<P>
Mejdani made this remark while meeting his Macedonian
counterpart, Kiro Gligorov, in Skopje, capital of Macedonia,
during his one-day tour of the country, according to the Albanian
Telegraphic Agency (ATA).
</P>
<P>
"The development of the region, its transformation into a space
of civil, not national states, where the high standard of living,
free education and other political and civic rights are respected,
should be our common objective," Mejdani was quoted by the ATA as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Albania supported a new Marshall plan covering not only
Albania, but also "a democratic Serbia," Mejdani noted.
</P>
<P>
The related pact of stability is the key to development and
stability in the region, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
The solution of the Kosovo conflict gave a clear response to
many issues and a new more advanced era in the Albanian-Macedonian
relationship should begin, he added.
</P>
<P>
The ATA reported that there were some differences between
Albania and Macedonia on the future status of Kosovo. Gligorov
backed a wider-ranging autonomy for Kosovo without changes of
borders, while Mejdani said that it will not hurt the relations
between Albania and Macedonia.
</P>
<P>
Mejdani also met with Macedonian Parliament Speaker Savo
Klimovski. He stressed that the parliaments of both countries
should support and encourage the cooperation between the two
countries and implementation of agreements signed between the two
governments.
</P>
<P>
Mejdani also said that Albanians should be represented in the
entire Macedonian administration. He asked the Macedonian
parliament to back the rights of the Albanians in Macedonia.
</P>
<P>
Klimovski expressed his support for intensified contacts
between the two parliaments. 
</P>
