on the U.S. embassies in Kenya and Tanzania last August, Osama was
listed in the top ten most wanted persons by the Federal Bureau of
Investigation last month.
</P>
<P>
The Saudi dissident left his dwelling in Kandahar in February
this year and then the Taliban kept saying that they did not know
where he was.
</P>
<P>
But the United States recently claimed that they found new
bases of Osama in Afghanistan and decided to impose economic
sanctions on the Taliban who they said are still supporting the
suspected terrorist.
</P>
<P>
Maulvi said, "Taliban are ready for talks with the United
States on Osama, but they are not listening to us."
</P>
<P>
He said the Taliban can not extradite Osama because they do not
have any extradition treaty with any country.
</P>
